messages.message: Do we have a definitive list of file formats that we support as input? And conversely, the same list but for output?
@Jesika Haria Do you happen to know if this is still up to date? https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FQ2kRIJNQ6Mxayv1RU7MXrujgf8gVCAk18Is3Kt24pM/edit#
This is 6 months old, but a lot of it hasn’t changed. What has is the addition of .ibdoc

I would _LOVE_ it if someone from engineering/support took over the reigns of maintaining this. I think it’s actually a really good internal resource, and I didn’t do as much marketing as I should have :stuck_out_tongue:

Awesome, thanks (see me dodge that “take this over” question? I’m like a meercat, I’m so slick).

Second question: the only thing that _outputs_ PDF (according to that doc) is Diff Checker. Is that still true?
@here Anyone else in here able to help me out with this? Specifically looking for additions to our supported file format list, and whether anything other than `Diff Checker` outputs PDF.
I’ve suggested the changes, feel free to accept unless there’s something you two want to confirm/clarify/etc.

but here’s an example of `apply_refiner` output: https://www.instabase.com/chetan/my-repo/fs/Instabase%20Drive/redactor%20multipage/template/out/s2_apply_redactor/

here’s an example of the refiner app output: https://www.instabase.com/chetan/my-repo/fs/Instabase%20Drive/redactor%20multipage/template/out_test/
Unfortunately I don’t have access to your repo to view the example outputs. Are those “text” PDFs or “image” PDFs that we output? I’m assuming “image” for redactor.
Image yes. I'll share it with you - - what's the instabase id?
